els (beta 0.396, p = 0.007) (S1 Table).", "bbox": [252.5, 727.8, 681.0, 741.7]}, {"text": "ROC curve analysis revealed that copeptin exhibited an increased overall ability to differen-", "bbox": [267.6, 744.2, 723.6, 758.1]}, {"text": "tiate between children with FS and controls compared to prolactin (AUC 0.824, 95% CI 0.753–", "bbox": [252.5, 760.7, 724.8, 774.6]}, {"text": "0.881 vs. 0.667, 95% CI 0.585–0.742; p <0.001) (Fig 2A). The discriminatory ability of copeptin", "bbox": [252.5, 777.0, 726.6, 791.0]}, {"text": "was enhanced when only children with FS who presented within 120 minutes from the event", "bbox": [252.5, 793.4, 714.0, 807.4]}, {"text": "were included in the analysis (AUC 0.879, 95% CI 0.806–0.932). In that case, the diagnostic", "bbox": [252.5, 809.9, 707.4, 823.8]}, {"text": "performance of copeptin was also superior to prolactin (AUC 0.690, 95% CI 0.598–0.772;", "bbox": [252.5, 826.3, 697.3, 840.2]}, {"text": "p < 0.001) (Fig 2B). Serum copeptin exhibited the maximum diagnostic ability when only chil-", "bbox": [252.5, 842.7, 725.0, 856.6]}, {"text": "dren with FS who presented within 60 minutes from the event were analyzed (AUC 0.975, 95%", "bbox": [252.5, 859.2, 725.3, 873.1]}, {"text": "CI 0.913–0.997), which was again significantly higher as compared to prolactin (AUC 0.729,", "bbox": [252.5, 875.5, 712.1, 889.5]}, {"text": "PLOS ONE | DOI:10.1371/journal.pone.0124663 April 20, 2015 5 / 11", "bbox": [45.5, 945.2, 727.3, 956.7]}]}